  "prompt": "What are all time best movies to watch?",
  "response": "Selecting the \"best\" movies can be subjective, as it largely depends on personal taste. However, many films are often cited as must-watch classics or significant achievements in cinema. Here's a list of some of the most acclaimed movies from various genres and eras:\n\n### Classic Cinema\n1. **\"Citizen Kane\" (1941)** - Often regarded as the greatest film ever made.\n2. **\"Casablanca\" (1942)** - A timeless romantic drama set during World War II.\n3. **\"Gone with the Wind\" (1939)** - An epic historical romance.\n4. **\"The Godfather\" (1972)** - A landmark in gangster films and cinema in general.\n5. **\"Lawrence of Arabia\" (1962)** - A sweeping historical epic.\n\n### Modern Classics\n1. **\"Pulp Fiction\" (1994)** - Quentin Tarantino's influential crime drama.\n2. **\"The Shawshank Redemption\" (1994)** - A powerful story of hope and friendship.\n\n### Science Fiction & Fantasy\n1. **\"Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope\" (1977)** - A groundbreaking space opera that launched a legendary franchise.\n2. **\"Blade Runner\" (1982)** - A seminal work in the science fiction genre.\n3. **\"The Matrix\" (1999)** - Influential for its special effects and storyline.\n4. **\"The Lord of the Rings\" series (2001-2003)** - Acclaimed epic fantasy films directed by Peter Jackson.\n\n### Drama\n1. **\"Schindler's List\" (1993)** - A poignant depiction of the Holocaust.\n2. **\"Forrest Gump\" (1994)** - A wide-ranging portrayal of historical events through the eyes of a unique character.\n\n### Comedy\n1. **\"Some Like It Hot\" (1959)** - A classic comedy featuring Marilyn Monroe, Tony Curtis, and Jack Lemmon.\n2. **\"Monty Python and the Holy Grail\" (1975)** - Renowned for its absurd and hilarious take on the Arthurian legend.\n\n### Thrillers\n1. **\"Psycho\" (1960)** - Alfred Hitchcock\u2019s groundbreaking thriller.\n2. **\"Seven\" (1995)** - A gripping psychological thriller with a dark narrative.\n\n### Animation\n1. **\"Spirited Away\" (2001)** - Hayao Miyazaki's fantastical and critically acclaimed animated film.\n2. **\"Toy Story\" (1995)** - The first entirely computer-animated feature-length film.\n\nThese films are celebrated for their storytelling, innovation, direction, and cultural impact. They span a broad range of genres, ensuring there\u2019s something for everyone to discover and appreciate.",
